<br>
1) Hibs are much slower at taking back keeps than Mids, so lets target a hid keep.<br>
<br>
2) Once a keep is held until 12am EST will normal stay in albs hand until 12-5pm the next day.<br>
<br>
3) the keeps closes to the pk are worth more rp per hour.<br>
<br>
So if we take a value 5 hib keep and hold it for 10 to 16 hour we will earn 50k to 80k rp for only 1000 - 1300 BP. Plus if we are able to get back to it the next day and defend it we should be able to earn more rp. <br>
<br>
Please note, that I think that we should only claim one more keep until we know what guild houses will cost. We can pratice taking and defending more keeps if we want, but I really don't want to spend BP until I know for sure what guild housing will cost; be it gold or BP or some other method.<br>
<br>
<br>
Nimitz<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uapo44.showPublicProfile?language=EN>apo44</A> at: 5/7/02 10:29:19 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6B8E23><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uaroqua.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aroqua</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(5/7/02 10:40:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1117.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Idea for next keep taking</span><hr size=1> Well we have captured a Mid keep and the defense of it started within 2 hours of taking, and with a good force arriveing to take it back. I too would suggest taking a Hib Keep, but lets do it when we can have people on for a while to defend the keep and get RP and BP's on defense. If we do this we can have someone keep track of the BP's that the guild has and determine if it will be beneficial for us to take another Keep. Basically, decide what we want our lowest limit to be, for example take 1600 from what we have curently and set that as the point we do not go below. If we can defend the keeps while we control them, we can most likely get a decent build up of the BP's we spent. <br>
<br>
Just suggestions on my part.<br>
<br>
Aroqua <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uaroqua.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aroqua</A> at: 5/7/02 10:41:22 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Wamba the Humble</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(5/7/02 11:10:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1117.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> reply</span><hr size=1> I am no expert, but I like your thinking guys.<br>
