<br>
Given the choice, I think that we might want to try attacking from a keep, rather then defending.<br>
<br>
I think that it was Creepy that posted about Keeps being pretty worthless to defenders, other then actually defending the lord's room. But they do hold one value: People tend to bunch up in front of the doors.<br>
<br>
I wonder if we would have a better chance by waiting for the bad guys to group up in front of the keep and then jumping into the middle of them with mez spells raging. Assuming that we could land even one mez spell there, we could probably then run <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> through</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> them and into their backfield to play hell with them for a minute.<br>
<br>
Hehe. Given that thought, we might even be able to mez the front folks (you with me on this Raj?) Then mez their back folks. run back there and kill them for one full minute, then run back to our little fort and get back in before they could do much.<br>
<br>
Finally, mezzing any folks may work well for an archer/assassin/tank team to walk through and take one or two kills. With archer, caster, and cleric support from the walkways above the gate, the casters should be held at bay. Anyone that approaches can take a mez or an arrow themselves. If one of our tanks leads with a shield stun and then gets in a whack or two, an infiltrator may be able to take the final kill shot and not even unstealth. (I don't know squat about infil's. Forgive me if I am talking crap).<br>
<br>
It would be an all-or-nothing play but could result in some decent RP's and, if we managed to kill their healers we would break the back of their offensive power. Tanks don't operate long in RvR without healers to keep them polished and looking like new.<br>
<br>
If it did not work, we would die all the same. At least this way we take the attack to them on our terms.<br>
<br>
Ok, flame away! Teach me, oh great RvR folks!<br>
<br>
Cheers, <p>Niz, Tavik, etc...<BR>
